A.D. 500) near Arica, Chile (Figure 1), the portrayal of this feature among the ceramic figures of Peru's Moche culture (A.D. 100-800) (Lumbreras 1974:102), as well as the presence of coca-leaf tomb offerings (Aufderheide 1990; Phillips and Wynne 1980:6) all provide further archaeological evidence of the importance of coca-leaf chewing among later populations. 
